args: Our kid is really into pirates, so that'd\nreally complete her look. Is that doable?
Shouldn't be an issue. I'll procure\none and deliver it on Dragonyule.
Phew. Okay, all that's left...are the\nkids I was told to just ask directly.
I'll try talking to those young ladies over\nthere first.
There's no need for alarm, miss. My name\nis Victor. I just have a quick question.

Behind me, Sister! Haven't I always told
you not to talk to strangers on the street?
Especially with all the rumors of thieves
on the loose of late...
I assure you, my intentions are pure. I just\nwant to ask if there's anything you wa—
Stay back! I know your game.\nYou just want to lure us in with shiny\nbaubles, and then BOOM! Kidnapped!
Then you stuff us in a big sack and whisk\nus off to some far off land to be sold on \nthe black market!
Please calm down. I don't intend anything\nof the sort. If you would just listen—
I can't heear you! LA LA LA LA!\nLet's book it, Sis!
What in the world was that about?
We saw the whole thing, sir. With respect,\nyou should leave this one to us.
You again. So, you think you can get\nthem to tell you what they want?
No doubt. You come off as a big hulking\nbrute. We're much more approachable.
Not sure I agree, but...fine.\nGive it a shot.
Hello there, little ladies! Why, it's almost\nDragonyule, isn't it? And that means\ngifts! What are you hoping for this year?
Let me guess: you want something too.
We are but humble census takers, traveling\nthe land tallying people and households,\nand surveying their wants and needs.
That's right! We're centaurs!\nEr...censors? Wait, what was it?
Threat level raised to red.\nC'mon, Sis. Let's ditch these guys too.
No, wait! If we can't get accurate data,\nwe'll be in big trouble! They'll...kill us!

Our manager is a terrible man. If his
employees don't deliver results, he chews
them up and spits them out like a wad of
used gum!
Wait, for real?! That IS awful.\nSave us, Boss! I'm too young to die!
Me too! But if these kids don't tell us\nwhat they want, then it's curtains for us.
So please, little lady... Tell us\nwhat you want, if only to save us.
And if...we tell you...\nWe won't get killed?
Hmmm. I GUESS we can do that.
So there you have it, good sir—\nthe info you require!
Aw, that was so sweet, Boss! Little kids\nsharin' their hopes and dreams...\nIt was so pyoo... Pyuh...
Pure? Indeed it was. Confronted with \nuncorrupted youth, one can't help but\nwant to protect it.
(I think we've won Mr. Meathead's trust.\nAll that's left is to do our thieving on\nDragonyule and lay the blame on him!)
Good work. I expect you to be just as\nthorough with the next one.
According to my list, there's still... Gene,\nLian, Sarasa... Seis, Siete, and Ocho.
Wait, wait, wait. There are more?! And we\nhave to ask ALL of them what they want?
That's what you volunteered for, yes. Now,\nmove out. I'll take that house over there.
Comet, are we really gonna do this?
Nrgh... Yeah. It's the only way to make\nour plan work. Let's go, Prancer!
Oh, Captain. How can I help you today?
I wanted to ask you what Daniil wants for\nDragonyule.
Hm. I think his granddad would know. \nCome in, come in.
Dear, has Daniil mentioned to you\nwhat he wants for Dragonyule this year?
Oh, hello, Captain! You know, I asked\nthe boy, but he wouldn't tell me.
He said he'd only tell Saint Starfall.
He must think if he tells anyone else,\nhis wish won't come true.
Another guest? Who is it now?
Noelle? What is it? Orders from home?
Um... Yes, there's a letter for you from\na...certain someone.
A missive from Litvinov, then.\n...Hey. That's it, Noelle!
Daniil asked me to deliver this letter...\nto Saint Starfall.
Bingo. Now, I know it's improper to open\nother people's mail. But right now, I'm\nexactly who this letter was intended for.
Mhm, mhm... I see.\nSo that's what Daniil is after.
Hm. This...will be a hard present to find.
